# CARL Opus 4.7 Domain
# =====================
# Drop at ~/.carl/opus-4-7 and register in ~/.carl/manifest with:
#   OPUS-4-7_STATE=active
#   OPUS-4-7_ALWAYS_ON=true
#
# These rules load on every prompt and encode Opus 4.7 behavior policy
# for any agent reading the CARL-injected context block.

OPUS-4-7_RULE_0=MODEL POLICY: When spawning agents or making direct SDK calls, Opus tier = claude-opus-4-7, Sonnet = claude-sonnet-4-6, Haiku = claude-haiku-4-5. No aliases in production-critical paths.
OPUS-4-7_RULE_1=EFFORT POLICY: Global default is high. For deep-reasoning skills (planning, research, build, design, brainstorm, debug, review) set xhigh explicitly when invoking Opus 4.7 via Messages API.
OPUS-4-7_RULE_2=THINKING POLICY: On Opus 4.7, {type:"enabled", budget_tokens:N} returns 400. Use {type:"adaptive"} with effort as the depth lever. Default display=omitted; set "summarized" only when a skill surfaces reasoning to the user.
OPUS-4-7_RULE_3=SAMPLING POLICY: Never pass temperature / top_p / top_k on Opus 4.7 (non-default returns 400). Guide via prompting only.
OPUS-4-7_RULE_4=TOKENIZER POLICY: Opus 4.7 tokenizer yields 1.0-1.35x more tokens per input. Add >=35% headroom to max_tokens vs pre-4.7 defaults. Minimum 64k at xhigh/max.
OPUS-4-7_RULE_5=PREFILL POLICY: No assistant-message prefills on Opus 4.7. Use structured outputs or system instructions instead.
OPUS-4-7_RULE_6=SCAFFOLDING POLICY: Opus 4.7 ships built-in progress updates and calibrated response length. Do not add "after every N tool calls report progress" or global "be concise" scaffolding -- let the model calibrate. When found in existing prompts, strip only if clearly redundant.
